<h1 id=3D"why-pasting-into-the-folder-failed">Why pasting into the folder f=
ailed</h1>
<p>Windows File Explorer does not let you paste <strong>plain copied text</=
strong> as a file automatically.</p>
<p>It only pastes:</p>
<ul>
<li>copied files</li>
<li>copied folders</li>
<li>images in some cases</li>
</ul>
<p>But here you copied <strong>text content</strong>, not an actual file ob=
ject.</p>
<p>So you must:</p>
<ol>
<li>paste into an editor</li>
<li>save as a file</li>
</ol>
<hr>
